      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ACTIVE DREAMS (1) has been in the frame at her last two runs, most recently when third (20.40) in a Grade 5 over 350m at Goulburn. Safe beginner and drawn well on the inside. Can make amends this time. GO FORWARD BLAZE (3) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a strong early split last time, paving the way for a half a length win at Gunnedah over 340m in 19.93. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. MISS SOUTHBROOK (6) comes off an average effort last start when seventh at this track over 318m behind Aston Joe (19.24) in a Grade 5. Was a winner the start prior. Strong form has emerged from her last run. One of the better chances. LAST STRAW (8) was out of the money here last time out but can bounce back.",
